@Luap99  If you are referring to `/etc/cni/net.d/*.conflist` then here it is

<details>
<summary>
Here is the CNI config
</summary>

```
{
   "cniVersion": "0.4.0",
   "name": "lz",
   "plugins": [
      {
         "type": "bridge",
         "bridge": "cni-podman1",
         "isGateway": true,
         "ipMasq": true,
         "hairpinMode": true,
         "ipam": {
            "type": "host-local",
            "routes": [
               {
                  "dst": "0.0.0.0/0"
               }
            ],
            "ranges": [
               [
                  {
                     "subnet": "10.89.0.0/24",
                     "gateway": "10.89.0.1"
                  }
               ]
            ]
         }
      },
      {
         "type": "portmap",
         "capabilities": {
            "portMappings": true
         }
      },
      {
         "type": "firewall",
         "backend": ""
      },
      {
         "type": "tuning"
      },
      {
         "type": "dnsname",
         "domainName": "dns.podman",
         "capabilities": {
            "aliases": true
         }
     }
   ]
}
```
</details>

@baude  I installed `dnsmasq` before creating the network.

@baude the network's name is `lz`.

I was sanitizing the data by replacing `lz` with `test`.

`lz` and `test` have the same config. Apologies for the confusion
